 Parole Board is reviewing the case of Colin Pitchfork , who was jailed for life in 1988 for raping and killing two schoolgirls .
He strangled 15-year-old Lynda Mann to death after raping her on a deserted footpath in 1983 .
Pitchfork was finally caught two years later thanks to DNA tests on all the men in surrounding villages .
He received a 30-year minimum sentence was cut to 28 years in 2009 , meaning he was eligible for release next year .